name: Michael Teach
bio: Smallmouth fishing, Quetico Provincial Park, Boundary Waters Canoe Area, Great Miami River, Outdoor Writer and Poet.

social_posts.post_text: Big December smallmouth from the Great Miami River 🎣 Special thanks to @officialmauijim for always keeping my eyes shaded. Best fishing shades I have ever owned! 😎
This has to be one of the best December’s I have ever had smallmouth fishing in the Great Miami River! 😎🎣. Special shout-out to @officialmauijim for making the best fishing shades on the market!
Another nice smallmouth from the Great Miami River this December! Caught her before the river froze over.
Love the colors on these February smallmouth from the Great Miami River! @officialmauijim

It’s been a great February on the Great Miami river so far this year! The warmer temperatures have these big girls moving up in the water column. Special shout-out to @officialmauijim for the awesome fishing shades hanging around my neck. It’s awesome the way they cut glare! 😎🎣
The river has been high and muddy here all month, so here’s a decent one from last month. Special shout-out to @officialmauijim for making the fishing shades in the market! 😎🎣

A nice smallmouth from the Great Miami River before it was flooded out!
Special shout out to @firstcastapparel for the new hoodie, @aquazwaders for always keeping me dry and @officialmauijim for the best fishing shades in the world 🌎😎🎣
I was interviewed by the @boundarywatersjournal and was named part of the Boundary Waters Canoe Angling Dream Team. You can obtain a copy @boundarywatersjournal or call 800-548-7319 🛶🎣

text_entities.entity: boundary waters canoe angling dream team

social_posts.post_text: A nice river smallmouth caught on a @booyah_baits Chartreuse glow willow blade spinner bait. Special mentions to @officialmauijim for having the best fishing sunglasses worldwide and @aquazwaders for always keeping me dry! 😎🎣

It was like setting the hook on a brick wall after I saw this smallmouth suck up my @zmanfishingproducts ShadZ in some fast current. Always thankful to be wearing my @aquazwaders and @officialmauijim gear! 😎🎣
Caught this smallmouth in the Great Miami River. The bottom half of the fish is all black on both sides. I have caught plenty with black spots, but never one with solid black for half the fish!
null
Just returned from a fantastic wilderness adventure in Quetico Provincial Park! The smallmouth fishing was spectacular!
New spinning smallmouth combination. @fish_shimano_north_america Vanford 2500 spinning reel paired with @fishgloomis NRX + 782 S rod.
Another big Quetico smallmouth caught on the @strikekinglurecompany KVD 2.5 wake bait! Thank God for @officialmauijim sunglasses, it was a very sunny trip and these shades helped immensely! 😎🎣
Just another big ole bronze bass from the Quetico! Special shout-out to @boundary_waters_catalog and @piragisoutfitting ! Thanks @officialmauijim for keeping me shaded during this sunny adventure!

First time I have caught a hybrid white bass \ striped bass (aka wiper) from the Great Miami river. Never heard of or seen anyone else ever catch one this far north on the river. @booyah_baits need to sponsor me for the big fish I catch on the chartreuse glow spinner bait. Special shout-outs to @fishgloomis and @fish_shimano_north_america .
Had the song Undun stuck in my head all day. I’m glad this one didn’t come undone 😂
A nice Quetico smallmouth on the ole Zulu rig while working an inflow to the lake🎣🛶

It’s like a fishing dream when you use @fishgloomis NRX plus rod combined with a @fish_shimano_north_america Vanford reel. Click my profile link for more info. She was caught on a KVD natural shad wake bait. Love topwater fishing! 🎣
Put some new treads on the ‘65 Impala and drove my Chevy to the levee🔥🏁🏁

The smallmouth were crushing the chartreuse spinner bait! Special shout-outs to @fish_shimano_north_america @fishgloomis 
@aquazwaders

My biggest smallmouth in the Boundary Waters last week! Caught on a frog colored Berkeley 130 Chopo! 🎣😎 Special shoutouts go to @fishgloomis and @fish_shimano_north_america for the ultimate combo! Check the first video on my page for more info on this combination!
Another topwater smallmouth beauty from the Boundary Waters! Special thanks to @fish_shimano_north_america and @fishgloomis. For more info on the combo I use check out my first post on my page! 🎣👍🏻

Beautiful Boundary Waters Bronze! I was using the @fishgloomis IMX Universal Walleye rod. It’s a two piece rod so I can break it down for portaging across the wilderness trails. This rod can handle the Grand Slam of any the massive pike, lake trout, walleye and smallmouth. It was paired with a @fish_shimano_north_america Vanford 3000 spinning reel. 🛶🎣

A nice topwater smallmouth caught on the KVD 2.5 wake bait while doing some bank fishing! Special shout-out to @kalkal_lena from @kalkalboots.official for supplying me with these durable, light weight and great traction boots. These will be awesome in late fall and winter bank fishing trips! (See second photo).
Beautiful river bronze caught on topwater! Was using the KVD 2.5 wake bait. Special shoutouts to @aquazwaders (check profile link) and @8fans.official for the wading boots I’m testing for them!

Loving the Fall colors! The big girls are getting a little more aggressive. Should get pretty good after the first frost. Special shoutouts to @aquazwaders for always keeping me dry. @8fans.official for their non-slip grip boots, and the best rods and reels from @fishgloomis and @fish_shimano_north_america . Check profile links for a retailer near you!

A nice bronze bass from the Great Miami river! Special shoutouts to @aquazwaders for keeping me dry! @8fans.official for the non slip wading boots. The best rod and reel combination @fish_shimano_north_america @fishgloomis
A chunky Boundary Waters smallie I forgot to post after the last trip! Hurry up month of May, I need to get back up into Quetico! 🛶🎣

You can find truly handcrafted customized lures at @custombaitshop ! I told them I was looking for a swim bait that looks like a local creek chubs and sent them a picture of the bait fish. They created their own stencils and patterns by hand from my picture! The craftsmanship and quality of these lures are like no other on the market! If you have an idea or a picture of a bait fish that would like to replicate, contact @custombaitshop today and have them create a truly one of a kind custom lure for you! custombaitshop.com
A nice Great Miami river smallmouth for December! If it’s above 35 I will be out there chasing ‘em 🎣 Special shoutout to @kalkalboots.official boots for keeping my feet warm and dry!

Pick up my new article today at @boundarywatersjournal or call 218-365-6184.
